  "prompt": "Which are the best institutes in Germany for masters in automotive engineering?",
  "response": "Germany is renowned for its automotive industry and offers several top institutes for pursuing a Master's degree in Automotive Engineering. Here are some of the best institutes to consider:\n\n1. **Technical University of Munich (TUM)**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Automotive Engineering\n   - **Overview**: TUM is one of Germany's leading technical universities, offering a highly regarded Master's program in Automotive Engineering. The program covers aspects of vehicle technology, propulsion systems, and vehicle safety.\n   - **Location**: Munich\n\n2. **RWTH Aachen University**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Automotive Engineering\n   - **Overview**: Known for its strong industry connections, RWTH Aachen's program focuses on vehicle systems, propulsion technology, and advanced engineering techniques.\n   - **Location**: Aachen\n\n3. **University of Stuttgart**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Automotive Engineering\n   - **Overview**: The University of Stuttgart offers a comprehensive program with a strong emphasis on research and development in automotive technologies.\n   - **Location**: Stuttgart\n\n4. **Technische Universit\u00e4t Braunschweig**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Automotive Engineering\n   - **Overview**: This program at TU Braunschweig emphasizes vehicle dynamics, powertrain systems, and automotive electronics.\n   - **Location**: Braunschweig\n\n5. **Darmstadt University of Technology (TU Darmstadt)**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Automotive Engineering\n   - **Overview**: TU Darmstadt provides a well-rounded program that covers vehicle engineering, manufacturing, and sustainability in automotive technologies.\n   - **Location**: Darmstadt\n\n6. **Berlin Institute of Technology (TU Berlin)**\n   - **Program**: M.Sc. in Vehicle Engineering\n   - **Overview**: TU Berlin's program focuses on vehicle systems, propulsion technology, and sustainable mobility solutions.\n   - **Location**: Berlin\n\nWhen choosing an institute, consider factors such as program curriculum, faculty expertise, industry connections, research opportunities, and the city's cost of living. Each of these universities offers a high-quality education and strong career prospects in the automotive industry.",
